						<summary>

						<p>Stone in a ruined temple, west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This Nāgarī record may be assigned on palaeographical considerations to c. 14th century.</p>						

						<p>This seems to record the construction of a temple <hi rend="italic">(kōṭi)</hi> probably to the deity Chāmuṇḍadēvī. Other details are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
